From 312ef977c6e8be0ee9636f325cfe2116ca176ec3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Philipp Stanner <phasta@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 23 Apr 2025 09:53:31 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: oxygen: Use pure devres PCI
Git-commit: 312ef977c6e8be0ee9636f325cfe2116ca176ec3
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: jsc#PED-14430 jsc#PED-14297 jsc#PED-14024

pci_request_regions() is a hybrid function which becomes managed if
pcim_enable_device() was called before. This hybrid nature is deprecated
and should not be used anymore.

Replace pci_request_regions() with the always-managed function
pcim_request_all_regions().

Signed-off-by: Philipp Stanner <phasta@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Andy Shevchenko <andriy.shevchenko@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250423075346.45907-14-phasta@kernel.org

---
 sound/pci/oxygen/oxygen_lib.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sound/pci/oxygen/oxygen_lib.c b/sound/pci/oxygen/oxygen_lib.c
index 9340d3c9ffd6..39b8ccf37cdd 100644
--- a/sound/pci/oxygen/oxygen_lib.c
+++ b/sound/pci/oxygen/oxygen_lib.c
@@ -609,7 +609,7 @@ static int __oxygen_pci_probe(struct pci_dev *pci, int index, char *id,
 	if (err < 0)
 		return err;
 
-	err = pci_request_regions(pci, DRIVER);
+	err = pcim_request_all_regions(pci, DRIVER);
 	if (err < 0) {
 		dev_err(card->dev, "cannot reserve PCI resources\n");
 		return err;
